        "title": "27. Demo",
        "transcriptMarkdown": "# Osteopathic Demonstration\n\nIn this demonstration, I take the **sacrum** quite low. My fingers are placed on the highest part you can feel. I don't grasp the entire sacrum, but low enough to reach the tip of the **notochord**.\n\nI flex and rock, all while observing. I apply good leverage with my elbow to get a good grip, a good **\"full crew\"**. It's very important not to create torsion, as this can be dangerous if the hand is placed too far, leading to rotation of the hand and pelvis.\n\nI position myself well in this axis, with a mental image of this **autobody**. I wait a moment and observe their breathing. I will gently enter another system, the one you described this morning.\n\nI feel it slightly deviates, veering to the left. A correction is gently taking place. I reconnect and wait, observing their breathing.\n\nThe door opens, I enter the **aptism** and await a small ascent. I seek to reconnect with this base, like with a laser. I'm talking too much and losing my train of thought.\n\nAs we have seen, this is a reference line. We discussed references for the **genome**, for the entire body, and for the formation of my posterior and anterior midline. This includes the entire **calcium** side, the strength at the level of **collagen** and **elastin**.\n\nWe also saw the power of the organisation of **asymmetry** and **polarity**. I seek to connect with this wave of life, and at some point, it gently works.\n\nI observe her eyes; she seems to be searching for images in her head. It's working, but the wave isn't there yet. I'm on a movement, a wave. Something is falling, and I feel I've reached my hand.\n\nHer eyes show that it's working. She might be releasing something related to a memory. I won't force it too much, as there's a reaction in the tissue. I go back down and wait.\n\nAgain, something is working. It has moved above the left breast, and her breathing has just changed, indicating a gentle oxidative change.\n\n## Sharing Sensations\n\nI ask the patient to share her sensations. She feels increased intensity. I will try to continue this video, as it takes time; sometimes it's fast, sometimes it's not. The idea is to have a sensation of **homogeneity**.\n\nFor now, something is working. I will give her a zero point so she knows what to do. I move to the right, remaining a welcoming point while being mobile to allow for relief.\n\nI remain attentive. At some point, something leaves, then I am there. This is the organism's system.\n\nFor now, it made a small movement, then it came back. It's starting to work at the head level. When I say I haven't finished the process, I mean I shouldn't calm down in relation to breathing.\n\n## The Zero Point\n\nThe zero point corresponds to the base of the skull, at the articulation between the **occiput** and the **sphenoid**. I take the occiput and my fingers go onto the greater wings of the sphenoid, looking for the **SSB** (sphenobasilar synchondrosis).\n\nI am at the centre of the SSB, below, above, throughout the SSB. I seek immobility, because it is a point created in immobility. I am not looking for a goal, but I always observe the breathing, the door, and the sensation behind.\n\nIt is important not to close your eyes when working, as this causes a 30% loss of information. I remain attentive to her gaze up to the edge of the field.\n\nI am careful not to say \"I see\". I remain outside, just in connection with the vibration. I look for a point of support for a reference, placing my attention on the base of the SSB.\n\nI am looking for **silence**. My touch is super light, an attentive listening. I gently move to the level of the skull to seek this point of dynamic immobility. This takes time, as the body needs to organise itself.\n\nI trust the principle of **osteopathy**. I must be neutral, and all of a sudden, I will be drawn to something. I don't enter the lesion; I let it pass.\n\nI stay with health, with the **fulcrum** of health. It is essential to put 30-40% of attention outside oneself and 70% inside. Willpower can sometimes be an obstacle, as it is often linked to our ego.\n\nIt is crucial to abandon this notion of wanting to do well to move towards this reference. The power of life is connected to this embryonic force. We are here to provide a point of support, and if necessary, it will take it or not.\n\nThis is not a technique I am teaching you, but a connection to the frequency."
