        "title": "44. Acid-Base Balance and the Hypothalamic-Pituitary System",
        "transcriptMarkdown": "# Acid-Base Balance and the Hypothalamic-Pituitary System\n\nWe will delve deeper into understanding the body in relation to its **acid-base balance**, its **nervous system**, and the chemistry of its tone.\n\nAt a certain point in its development, the body integrates a **thalamic** and **hypothalamic** level into its core.\n\n## Role of the Hypothalamus in Regulation\n\nThe **hypothalamus** plays a crucial role, at a deep neurological level, by performing **regulation**. This regulation redistributes a preferential tone, either **ergotrophic** or **trophotrophic**.\n\nCellular information, which arrives via an **oxidation-reduction** system or **cyclic AMP** and **cyclic GMP**, is integrated at the level of the hypothalamus. The latter then provides feedback.\n\nTo simplify, your acid-base terrain will be integrated, via the bloodstream, at the **hypothalamic-pituitary** level. This will transmit information related to your **limbic system** and your **Papez circuit**, re-integrating this into a tonality.\n\nThus, it will give you a side that is:\n\n* **Ergotrophic**: oriented towards work, **orthosympathetic**.\n* **Trophotrophic**: oriented towards recovery.\n\nThis manifests as a posture. Through a sympathetic or parasympathetic tone, the hypothalamus must be informed of the acid-base balance, expressing a **trophotrophic** or **ergotrophic** tone.\n\n## Integration of Acid-Base Balance\n\nAt the level of the hypothalamus, a predominant **acidosis** or **alkalosis** between tissues manifests itself. These are local adaptations integrated into intermediate, **diaphragmatic** levels, connected to continuously stimulated movements.\n\nThis means that we have **synaptic transmission** that carries information of the **cyclic AMP** or **gonadocyclic** type. These two types of transmission are expressed at the cellular level by a dynamic system, i.e., an oxidation-reduction system, or in other words, acid-base.\n\nThe whole is recovered at the neurological level, integrated into the **corticospinal pathway** and the **limbic pathway**. All memories, including your diet, are integrated at this level and provide a response.\n\n## Body Response and Posture\n\nThis response manifests in your system through the **paraventricular** or **supraoptic nuclei**, leading to a bodily response.\n\nFor example, you can go into a **left-right** or **right-left spiral**, and this will influence your **sphincters**.\n\nAt the level of your **pancreatic facial pentagon**, you have different areas with specific sphincters:\n\n* The **pyloric sphincter**.\n* The **duodenal sphincter**.\n* The **ileocecal sphincter**.\n* The **recto-anal sphincter**.\n\nThese sphincters integrate according to your movement. If you shift your centre of gravity to the right or to the left, you will have a different action on these sphincters.\n\nIf you are blocked, this affects your sphincters, which can be either open or closed. You can be experiencing **diarrhoea** or **constipation**, or be in a **precancerous** or **pro-inflammatory** state. All of this, whether you are in **para** or **ortho**, is reflected in specific chemistry.\n\nThe body tries to balance everything and equilibrate itself, putting you in a state of constipation or prompting you to open your centre and have diarrhoea.\n\nAll of this is expressed by this chemistry integrated at the hypothalamic level.\n\nIn your **chemico-postural** plan, we can observe phases of **external rotation** and phases of **internal rotation**.\n\nObservation of posture and balance allows us to read the body's chemistry. This is why the body continuously tries, through the act of breathing, to adapt to the environment programmed by its hypothalamic-pituitary system, located at the base of the skull."
