        "cloudflareId": "682f30474ce5bd68cfb9ddb8e11f45db",
        "duration": "08:15",
        "title": "1-Introduction_The WUWAI",
        "transcriptMarkdown": "# Introduction to the WUWAI of Biodynamic Embryology\n\n## Trust and Absence of Induction\n\nIn **biodynamic embryology**, the therapist intervenes very little through **direct induction**. It is more about trusting an inherent force that transcends us.\n\nNot giving induction and not actively intervening is a challenge, as classical learning has often taught us the opposite. We are not only in contact with the tissue but also with the surrounding **space**.\n\n## Primary Respiration and Primary Respiratory Movement\n\nA key concept is the distinction between **primary respiration** and **primary respiratory movement**. Primary respiration is omnipresent, not limited to the physical body, but present in the totality of existence.\n\nIt can be considered the **\"breath of life\"**. It is essential to experience this and dare to enter this space.\n\n## Principle of Health and Biodynamics\n\nBiodynamic embryology is part of one of the great principles of **osteopathy**: the body's capacity for **self-regulation** and its homeostatic principle of health.\n\nOur work in biodynamics is to work with health, rather than against disease. This is a paradigm shift, as we are often inclined to look for the lesion.\n\nMy approach invites you to seek health. This is not always easy, as the attraction to the lesion is strong. We do not disregard it, but we do not dwell on it.\n\n## The Secret: Discovering the Neutral\n\nThe secret to immersing oneself in this process is to discover what the **neutral** is.\n\n### Practitioner's Neutral\n\nFirstly, there is the **\"practitioner's neutral\"**. This is not simple, as we are not spontaneously in this state.\n\nI have progressively guided you towards a state of neutrality through **meditation**, the \"therapist's neutral\".\n\nThis state is necessary, but it is not yet sufficient to bring forth therapeutic power, nor to fully express the breath of life. The practitioner must first be centred and discover this neutral state.\n\n### Meeting of Neutrals\n\nOnce we have discovered this neutral state and are in contact with the patient, we must open our space to the different fields:\n\n*   **Zone A:** The physical body.\n*   **Zone B:** The fluidic system, which I have emphasised throughout the seminar.\n*   **Surrounding spaces:** The space we are in, then the different spaces up to the broadest image you can conceive.\n\nAfter the \"therapist's neutral\", the second step, and this is where the difficulty lies, is to bring forth the **\"patient's neutral\"**.\n\nThis is the key. You have your own neutral, but if the patient does not enter their own neutral, i.e., a state of disengagement, the therapeutic forces cannot emerge.\n\n### Emergence of Therapeutic Forces\n\nThe emergence of therapeutic forces occurs when these two neutrals meet. It is like the formation of \"one\" and \"two\" to reach the \"whole\", which could be called the **\"three\"**.\n\nWhen the therapist's neutral meets the patient's neutral, the therapeutic forces – primary respiration, the breath of life – allow the inherent power of the system to emerge.\n\nThis emergence manifests with the strength of its originality. It is at this moment that the encounter with embryonic forces occurs. It is the same energy that the body will seek to regenerate, restructure, and regain its function.\n\n## The Four Bodies\n\nWe will realise that we need to gradually bring people \"back to earth\".\n\n### 1. Force of Gravity (Contact with the Earth)\n\nThis is what is called the **force of gravity**. Being well anchored in one's force of gravity means being well in contact with the earth. This contact is very important.\n\nSome are too \"in the earth\", as if already \"buried\", while others are not \"on the earth\", they float. This fundamental contact must be restored.\n\n### 2. Electromagnetic Force (Bringing Back into the Body)\n\nNext, there is the **electromagnetic force**. This involves bringing people back into their bodies.\n\nFollowing shocks (such as whiplash or other accidents), it is possible for people to be \"out of their bodies\". Although not visible, they are as if disconnected. It is about bringing them back into their electromagnetic field.\n\n### 3. Energetic Body (The Atmos, Non-Form)\n\nThe third step is to bring people back into their **energetic body**, into the \"atmos\". The \"atmos\" represents non-form.\n\nThis energetic body is often perceived as a vibrational state, a frequency, a vibration.\n\n### 4. Body of Light (Full Function)\n\nFourth point, it is about bringing people back into their **body of light**. Being completely luminous means being fully in one's function.\n\nIt is therefore about bringing people back to their full functionality. The more you are in tune with this, the more you attract the right energy around you, what I call **\"right synchronicities\"**.\n\n## The \"Meeting Point\"\n\nTo reach this level, we need what is called the **\"meeting point\"**: a point of encounter between the therapist and the patient.\n\nIf there is no such meeting point, there is no therapeutic emergence. Sometimes we can treat patients without a real \"meeting point\" occurring; in this case, nothing essential will happen.\n\nSome patients arrive and we already know what we are going to do, but that is not a meeting point. The important thing is to discover and bring forth this neutral in your patient.\n\nThis requires a particular space and attention to the possibility of this emergence, through touch, presence, and alignment.\n\nWhen I work with a child, I always get down to their level to seek this meeting point. If this point is created, the child very quickly enters the emergence of their neutral.\n\nIt is then that the therapeutic force can begin to express itself.\n\n## Laws of Nature and Corrections\n\nWe do not impose, we seek the neutral, the patient's neutral. We surrender to what I call the **laws of nature**.\n\nIt is very important to have this trust in the process. Corrections will emerge through your presence, movements will occur.\n\nThese corrections are similar to what **Sutherland** described, and they are close to biodynamic movements and the motility of embryonic development. These are the same phenomena that will manifest.\n\n## Longitudinal Fluctuation\n\nThe first very important thing is to restart this **longitudinal fluctuation**. This is one of the primary powers the body uses.\n\nIf you study Sutherland, he talks about it, particularly when working at the base, to revitalise this longitudinal fluctuation.\n\n## The WUWAI: Non-Doing\n\nI repeat again: what is your neutral? I ask you this question: what is neutral for you? Because it is from this neutral that we will work.\n\nThis is where the Chinese have a fantastic word: **\"wu bei\"** (or **\"wu wei\"**). This does not mean \"doing nothing\", but rather \"not doing\" (**\"non-doing\"**). This is a very important distinction.\n\nSome therapists only use their knowledge, others rely more on their imagination. I ask you to use both.\n\nWe need this knowledge, your background, and we need this imagination. We must combine them and work progressively with them."
