        "title": "3-Introduction to the Mesoderm",
        "transcriptMarkdown": "# Introduction to the Mesoderm\n\nWhat happens here demonstrates the unity and **synchronicities** of development. The importance of this coiling around the **cardio-pleuroperitoneal cavity** is paramount. We can say that the **mesoderm** is a link between the **ectoderm** and the **endoderm**.\n\nThe therapeutic path and the practice path are a **mesodermal** path. These processes, these therapeutic lines, develop in a process of **growth**. It is a unique movement, not a succession of distinct movements. We can connect to this great movement.\n\n## The concept of growth and longitudinal developmental power\n\nIt is essential to observe this concept of **growth** and this **longitudinal developmental power**. This developmental power is a meeting between the inside and the outside, and vice versa.\n\nThe **therapeutic force** comes from the outside. The body has a capacity for **self-regulation** to maintain its health, and we work with that.\n\nIn the stomach, there are **villi**. These villi are made up of cells, a layer of **epithelial** cells. This layer contains cells that produce **mucus** and cells that produce **acids**.\n\nThere is always, and this is very common throughout the body, a layer of **stem cells**. In the stomach tissue, these are **regenerative** cells that use this power of self-regulation.\n\nRemember that your body is constantly regenerating. The **gastric mucosa**, the cells, the skin… all of this is constantly regenerating and using this embryonic power.\n\nThrough the encounter of neutrals, this principle I propose allows for the sublimation of this process. In this principle of **structure-function**, I speak of **form**.\n\nAm I in good shape today? This maintains this notion of health. The notion of **time**, the notion of **tissue**, and the notion of **fluids** are interrelated.\n\n## The importance of fluids in the body\n\nWhen we started studying **embryology**, I mentioned that your mental image was built around **bone**. In reality, our body is built around **fluids**.\n\nThis means that we are moving more and more towards the perception of this fluid body. In your body, you have **volumes** that can express a mental state. In fact, you function according to these volumes: these are the **voids** and the **fulls**.\n\n## Summary and course orientation\n\n1. **First session:** Study of the **notochordal axis** and the development of the **neural tube**.\n2. **Second session:** Study of the development of the **viscerocranium** and the importance of the **base of the skull** in this process.\n3. **Now:** We will essentially study everything in green, which we will call the **internal man**. That is, the entire **support system**, and especially the **fluid system**.\n\nI remind you that you are made up of a very large percentage of **water**. But how does this water get into the body?\n\nThis fluid body will be dependent on an **electrical body**. One could say: I first need something undifferentiated, then an **electrical field**, and finally a **structural field**.\n\nWe will first go into this void, to feel the electrical field, and to help the fluids restructure. Then, these fluids will **densify**.\n\nWe move from a level of **light** to a level of **density**, to one day rediscover our light.\n\n## The form of water and its therapeutic implications\n\n**70%** of body mass is **equids**. But water can express itself as **vapour**, as **gas**. There is water that can **crystallise**. This too is important: it is the **form of water**.\n\nYou have already heard of this Japanese study which, depending on thought, structured the quality of the form of water. This means that our **thoughts** are important.\n\nIt must be realised that water is **structured**, it is linked. This is what maintains **cohesion**. These phenomena give rise to **dried**, desiccated or hydrated fields.\n\nWhen we work at the level of the **brain**, of the **skull** on the fluid body, we will gradually learn to feel this energy level. Is the body dry or not?\n\n**Structural** techniques can momentarily dehydrate the body if not done consciously. On the other hand, **biodynamic** techniques tend to rehydrate the body.\n\nThis notion of **rebalancing** at the level of my **ions**, at the level of my **macromolecules**, on how water will structure itself, forms shells that provide cohesion.\n\nIf you have **dehydration** in your body, you lose your abilities. Remember that it takes **six months** to rehydrate. Rehydrating means drinking spring water, quality water. Biodynamics helps to restructure the body's water quality.\n\n## The Homunculus Interni and Mesodermal Trajectories\n\nThe **Homunculus Interni**, the mesodermal man, is linked to **trajectories**.\n\n- On the **vascular** level.\n- On the level of **urogenital** development trajectories.\n- On the development of **locomotor** trajectories.\n\nI like the idea of trajectory because it gives you therapeutic help and support for understanding."
