        "title": "10 - The Heart_3 External Information Gatherings",
        "transcriptMarkdown": "# The Heart: 3 External Information Inputs\n\nThis moment is crucial, as the **embryo** will accelerate its growth. We will observe a **complete coiling** of the brain, and, remarkably, three levels of **external information** will interact via this rhythmicity.\n\n## 1. Heart - Eyes Interaction\n\nFirstly, the brain will coil around the heart. Significant information is transmitted at the level of the **optic placodes**, directly to the heart. One could almost say that the **eyes** will \"settle\" on the heart.\n\n## 2. Heart - Hands Interaction\n\nYou will also see another interaction: the limb **buds** will come to rest on the heart. This fully informs the heart. Do not forget that the heart receives very important information at the level of the **neural crest**, an **electromagnetic** plane that allows us to feel the heart from a distance. This information will impregnate your hands on a rhythmic plane.\n\n## 3. Heart - Thyroid and Voice Interaction\n\nThere is another part that we do not see directly, but in this coiling, the entire **thyroid system** comes to rest on the heart. This is accompanied at some point by the opening of development upwards, which will form the **vocal cord system**. It is often said that the **tongue** is the bud of the heart. However, the tongue is linked to the thyroid and transmits information.\n\n## The Heart-Body Connection: Perception and Communication\n\nWhen I touch someone, I touch them with information received from my heart. I must maintain this connection. You will see that this will greatly change your perception.\n\n*   **The Gaze:** When I look at someone, I must look at them with my heart. The two are connected. The heart is informed on an embryonic level, receiving purely electromagnetic information.\n\n*   **Speech:** Thirdly, when I speak, I must speak with my heart. I receive this thyroid information, electrical information.\n\nI therefore have three magnetic fields of information. When we receive this information, we must be very attentive to:\n\n*   Our thoughts.\n*   Our touch.\n*   Our gaze.\n\nThis is first designed to receive, then to give. But the primary function comes from the **rhythm of the heart**, which gave your hand its **neurosensibility**. This heart acts in this way, then it opens. This is **love**, this is **joy**."
