        "transcriptMarkdown": "# Guided Practice: Zone B Work\n\nIn this practice, the objective is to find **health**, to work with it, and to fully trust the process of **self-regulation** generated by **primary respiration**, when the two neutrals merge.\n\nYou will make contact with the patient in the gentlest way possible. It's like asking for **communication**, for **permission**. The present movement is health.\n\n## Body Perception\n\nWe touch as if we had **ants** that could leave, but cannot, and that we cannot crush. Take your time, let your neutral mature further, position yourself perfectly.\n\nAllow **thoracic breathing**, and little by little primary respiration, to synchronise. Your hands are placed on the **micro-crystalline field**, meaning you encompass the entirety of the person, even their **aura**, their **amniotic cavity**. You hold the entirety of the person in your hand. Breathing moves, the breath of life moves, primary respiration, and the awareness of the space around you.\n\nThis respiration itself has a fulcrum point located in **Zone A**, within the body. Respiration is like a door opening and a door closing. If there is a door opening and a door closing, there is like a **hinge**, a fulcrum point for this respiration. You have silence or **dynamic stillness** in the room.\n\nYou have the breathing that moves and the breath of life, primary respiration. Little by little, your neutral deepens.\n\n## Synchronisation and Stillness\n\nYou synchronise with primary respiration, the breath of life, and your thoracic breathing. Simply synchronise.\n\nBecome aware of the **crystalline stillness** of the room. The fulcrum point, the still point of this pendulum, represents the point of stillness of thoracic respiration.\n\nYou remain in the space, in the presence of spatial awareness. You have in mind all this movement, the stillness that is there, and its transverse and longitudinal organisation.\n\nSomewhere, you will rebuild this layer. At the same time, you will restore all the strength of the **fluids** towards the centre.\n\nYou have breathing, the breath of life, and the awareness of the room. Stillness.\n\n## The Meeting of Neutrals\n\nLittle by little, with a little calm, when the neutral deepens, these two points of silence will merge. This will give a new quality: **silence**.\n\nFor this, you have observed the breathing, the end of exhalation. Just before the patient inhales again, there is an awareness, there is a door. Place yourself in this quality.\n\nBreathing, the crystalline stillness of the room, the breath of life, and the meeting, little by little, of this **diaphragm**, these **diaphragmatic pillars**, this fulcrum point of respiration, and this silence of the room, this stillness of the room.\n\nLittle by little, the neutrals must meet. They will merge, they will unify.\n\n## Reconstruction and Regeneration\n\nYou have the **amniotic cavity** expanding laterally, like an egg completely surrounding you and rebuilding itself. The entire fluid system recentres.\n\n- Zone A calms down.\n- Zone B rebuilds itself.\n- Zone C merges with stillness.\n\nWith the dynamic stillness of the fulcrum point of respiration. Let the neutral deepen.\n\nThis **midline**, like a function, is a centre of health. It is an opening to space, there is no real distance. Let yourself be placed by it. Open your perceptual, peripheral field.\n\n## The Therapeutic Function\n\nThe meeting of the two neutrals will create, open the **therapeutic function**. Now, it is the small tide that is present.\n\nLet yourself be repositioned by it. It cannot be harmed. This is what will allow, little by little, the correct spatio-temporal reorientation of form and its function. **Unity** with nature.\n\nIt converts therapeutic forces. Let this process continue for a few more minutes. Surrender yourself.\n\nThe amniotic cavity, Zone B, rebuilds itself. The body finds its fulcrum points, its points of silence to be reborn.\n\nThere is a full force of **regeneration** that is being set in motion, that is being activated.\n\n## Alignment and Awareness\n\nBring your awareness to the **horizon**. From your midline to the horizon. From the centre of your being to the horizon. From the horizon to your midline.\n\nBreathing, the breath of life. Little by little, there may be a **tight** that arrives. Let yourself be surprised.\n\nIt's like a warmth that will begin to enter. A **metabolic increase**. A **rebalancing**.\n\nIt's a mantra that cuts off the mind: Oum! O yā ā O vénā Vēnā Sī Nē O."
