        "title": "33- Practice_Reminders & Chain Work for the Stomach",
        "transcriptMarkdown": "# Practice: Reminders & Chain Work for the Stomach\n\nThe **digestive tract** extends from the mouth to the anorectal membrane. We have already explored the oesophagus, lungs, and now the stomach, taking into account its essential **packaging**, namely the **retrogastric pouch** and the **peritoneum**. The latter must be considered an **intelligent** element in our approach.\n\nWe will work from the **base of the skull** to the **oesophago-cardiotuberositary junction** of the stomach. It is also crucial to consider the support area at the **hyoid** level, in relation to the **fulcrum** of the oesophagus and its **embryological fulcrum**. The latter is represented by **Vinso's hiatus**, which resets itself each time.\n\nIt is important to look for **support points** so that the system organises itself efficiently in its function. We have identified several functions of the stomach: **hormonal**, **mechanical**, and **fluidic**. Furthermore, the stomach is related to **speech**. Its functioning begins in the mouth, with the tongue, saliva, teeth, and swallowing. This highlights the importance of not swallowing our words.\n\n**Anger** can be expressed, repressed, or enlighten us. If expressed, it can be problematic. If repressed, it is very bad. However, if we use it with clarity, it can enlighten us. At the moment anger rises, there is a vision that can be exploited to return to **clarity of mind**. Every emotion has its **wisdom** and can be transformed into **awakening**.\n\nWe observe a small **stomach ring** around the iris. Examining the lip, one can note a slight discolouration, as well as a pale and trembling tongue. To work on the stomach, we will start from the base of the skull, resuming the **dural sheath** while applying gentle pressure to look for the **rings** and allow **freedom**.\n\nWe will first address a **tissue** plane, then possibly a **cellular** plane, and if necessary, a **molecular**, **enzymatic**, or **energetic** plane. The work is done gently in relation to the **sphenobasilar symphysis**. A slight swelling in the neck lodge may indicate old stress related to the **adrenal glands**. We release through the kidneys and diaphragm, thus restoring **flexibility** to the diaphragmatic pillars.\n\nWe can also work on the **hyoid bone** in relation to its **embryonic fulcrum**. Tensions can be felt at the hypoglossal level, indicating **unspoken words** that can be released to facilitate expression. Taking into account the junction of the stomach, we can also work on the **sphenoid** to release tensions.\n\nThe stomach, in its entirety, is connected to the lesser sac of the **omentum**. By placing our hands on the posterior part of the stomach, we create a **gliding** surface to allow expression. We observe the patient's breathing, connecting to their breath. The work is done in the **void**, where we can receive information from the tissue.\n\nA gentle **transmutation** occurs, and it is possible to feel an odour emanating from the tissue, indicating a change. By working at the **sacrum**, we can explore the lesser pelvis, which can help realign the body. A strong heat can be felt, symbolising the alignment of ancestors.\n\nWe inscribe these corrections in the patient's brain, accessing the **limbic system** so that they retain this moment as an **eternity**."
